    <id>https://www.nber.org/papers/w34258</id>
    <title>Scale Economies, Input-Output Loops, and Trade</title>
    <updated>2025-09-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dominick G. Bartelme, Yuyang Jiang, Konstantin Kucheryavyy &amp; Andrés Rodríguez-Clare</name>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;b&gt; NBER Working Papers&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;This paper studies the equilibrium and welfare implications of quantitative trade models with sector-level external economies of scale (EES). While empirical evidence highlights the importance of EES, prior work has examined their effects only in models without input-output linkages. Focusing on a small open economy, we derive an intuitive condition for equilibrium uniqueness that links trade elasticities, scale elasticities, and input-output coefficients. We further show that this same condition guarantees positive gains from trade, regardless of a country’s pattern of specialization.</content>
